curve\". Can you create a new similar procedure in order to draw the symmetrical across the y-axis points of the points constructed by the procedure \"curve\"? Complete (or correct) the procedure \"curve2\" and test if you made it by running the following commands:\n\nclean\naxes\ncurve 4 10\npu home pd\ncurve2 4 10\n\nTASK 2:\nWhich modification must be done in the procedure \"curve\" in order to draw the points of the parabola  y=0.5*x^2?Complete (or correct) the procedure \"curve3\" and run the correct command in order to draw them.\n\nTASK 3:_______________________________\nFor each one of the following lines of commands, find the equation of the parabola whose points are constructed. \n\nclean axes curve 4 -30\nclean axes curve 6 -50\nclean axes curve 8 -70\n\n\nTASK 4:_______________________________\nStudy the following commands and make a conjecture on the formula of the parabola whose points will be constructed:\n\nclean \naxes\npu rt 90 fd 30 lt 90 pd\ncurve 6 -50\nThen run the commands to verify your conjecture.\n\n\n\nTIPS\n-----------------------\n\nTASK 2:\nTO curve3 :n :a\nbullet\nIf :n<1 [stop]\npu\nrt 90 fd 10 lt 90 fd :a\npd\ncurve3 :n-1 :a+10\nEND\n\nclean\ncurve3 4 5\n\n\n\n\n\n","sliders":{},"objects":[]}